                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6731/195: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-06T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 6, 1937—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Your 17, May 4, 5 p.m. If note contains detailed proposals please telegraph
                    summary. If the proposal is merely made in general terms is it your
                    understanding that concrete suggestions will be forthcoming from the Turkish
                    Government shortly?</p>
                <p>Since its telegram No. 1, November 19, 6 p.m., the Department’s views respecting
                    possible negotiations with Turkey have become sufficiently crystallized to
                    permit of early consideration by it of any concrete proposals which the Turkish
                    Government may have in mind. For tactical reasons, however, the Department still
                    wishes to leave the initiative with respect to detailed proposals entirely with
                    the Turks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
